column19: Immigration_Arrest_Circumstances__c
Was arrested by ICE officers when he was released from CTF Soledad

Leaving prison (state/federal) California City Correctional City Notes: ICE interviewed him in California City on ~1/3/23 but had no prior contact with ICE while in prison. DO picked him up in R and R on release date. Transferred and processed in Bakersfield.

Leaving prison (state/federal) State Penitentiary In Jamestown Notes: He had been working as a firefighter while in prison and thought he was going to be released. Two weeks before his release date from prison, he was notified that ICE wanted to talk to him and they detained him. He was transferred to the state Penitentiary in Jamestown before he was picked up by ICE.

Leaving prison (state/federal) Mule Creek State Prison Notes: He was supposed to be released but ICE put a hold on him because he refused to sign papers that he didn't understand. Then they lifted the hold, saying he wasn't going to be deported, but then right before he was supposed to be released ICE came to pick him up.

Leaving prison (state/federal) He Was At Julius 19 Klein Conservation Camp When He Received A Letter From Ice Then Was Transferred To Sierra Conservation Center Scc Notes: He was at Julius 19 Klein Conservation Camp for a year before getting transferred to SCC

At home Ice Went To His Home And Said That They Were The Police And That They Needed To Investigate Him Notes: When he came out of his home they immediately handcuffed him, ICE didn't tell him why they were there.

San Jose community arrest: Had left home for work. Was close to home when they stopped him. Around 7:30am.  He thought they were trying to pass him in the car so he pulled over to the side. Then they stopped their cars, pointed guns at him and told him to get out of the car.

Vehicle stop In Shafter, Ca. At 5:15 Am, Coworker Who Drives Him To Work Was Driving Him And They Were Stopped By Ice. Ice Had Warrant For Alberto. Transferred Him To Bakersfield Field Office And Processed Him There. Did Not See The Warrant Himself But They Said His Daca Was Expired And That Is Why They Detained Him. Pulled Him Over At Shafter Ave And Elizabeth St. At A Stop Sign. Two Ice Vehicles Pulled Them Over. Let The Driver Go But Detained Him. Notes:
